        <name>1.2.2.4  Remove brackets</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Remove the brackets from the following expressions, leaving your answer in the simplest form:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(({@a1@}a)^2=\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(({@b1@}ab)^3=\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;\({@c1@}(ab)^3=\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(({@d1@}xy)^4=\) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Removing the brackets we obtain:&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;\( ({@a1@}a)^2 = {@a1@}^2 \cdot a^2 = {@ta1@}. \)&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Removing the brackets we obtain:&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;\( ({@b1@}ab)^3 = {@b1@}^3 \cdot a^3 \cdot b^3 = {@ta2@}. \)&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;This time, \({@c1@}\) is not in the brackets, so using the third law of indices we obtain:&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;\( {@c1@}(ab)^3 = {@ta3@}. \)&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Again, removing the bracket gives: &lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;\( ({@d1@}xy)^4 = {@d1@}^4 \cdot x^4 \cdot y^4 = {@ta4@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
